definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  4-cresol + acceptor + H2O -eq- 4-hydroxybenzaldehyde + reduced acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction -  carbonyl sulfide + 2 H+ + 2 e- -eq- hydrogen sulfide + carbon monoxide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  vinyl chloride + 2 H+ + 2 e- -eq- HCl + ethene.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1,1,1-trichloroethane + 2 H+ + 2 e- -eq- 1,1-dichloroethane + HCl.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-chloro-N-isopropylacetanilide + H+ + 2 e- -eq- Cl- + N-isopropylacetanilide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  organohalide + 2 H+ + 2 e- -eq- R-H + HCl. Reactants include chlorohydroquinone (forms hydroquinone) and 2,5-dichlorohydroquinone (forms chlorohydroquinone).

Catalysis of the reaction -  1,1-dichloro-2,2-bis(4-chlorophenyl)ethene + H+ + 2 e- -eq- Cl- + 1-chloro-2,2-bis(4-chlorophenyl)ethene. 1,1-dichloro-2,2-bis(4-chlorophenyl)ethene is also known as DDE -  1-chloro-2,2-bis(4-chlorophenyl)ethene is also known as DDMU.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2,4-dichlorophenoxyacetic acid + H+ + 2 e- -eq- Cl- + 4-chlorophenoxyacetate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1,2-dichloroethene + 2 H+ + 2 e- -eq- HCl + vinyl chloride.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1,2,3,5-tetrahydroxybenzene + 1,2,3-trihydroxybenzene -eq- 1,3,5-trihydroxybenzene + 1,2,3,5-tetrahydroxybenzene.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1-phenanthrol + X-CH3 -eq- X + 1-methoxyphenanthrene.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + a thiol -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + a thioether.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetone + ATP + CO(2) + 2 H(2)O -eq- acetoacetate + AMP + 4 H(+) + 2 phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  benzoyl acetyl-CoA + CoA -eq- acetyl-CoA + benzoyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-hydroxy-5-oxohexanoyl-CoA + CoASH -eq- 3-hydroxybutyryl-CoA + acetyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-ketopimeloyl-CoA + CoA -eq- glutaryl-CoA + acetyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  9-phenanthrol + UDP-glucuronate -eq- 9-phenanthryl-beta-D-glucuronide + UDP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1-phenanthrol + glucose -eq- 1-phenanthryl-beta-D-glucopyranoside + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  9-phenanthrol + glucose -eq- 9-phenanthryl-beta-D-glucopyranoside + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1,2-dihydroxyphenanthrene + UDP-glucose -eq- 2-hydroxy-1-phenanthryl-beta-D-glucopyranoside + UDP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  6-aminohexanoate + alpha-ketoglutarate -eq- glutamate + 6-oxohexanoate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  phenol + X-HPO3- -eq- XH + phenylphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  trans-9R,10R-dihydrodiolphenanthrene + 2 X-SO3(-) -eq- 2 HX + phenanthrene-9,10-dihydrodiolsulfate conjugate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1-phenanthrol + X-SO3(-) -eq- HX + 1-phenanthrylsulfate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-phenanthrol + X-SO3(-) -eq- HX + 3-phenanthrylsulfate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  4-phenanthrol + X-SO3(-) -eq- HX + 4-phenanthrylsulfate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  trans-3,4-dihydrodiolphenanthrene + 2 X-SO3(-) -eq- 2 HX + phenanthrene-3,4-dihydrodiolsulfate conjugate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  9-phenanthrol + X-SO3(-) -eq- HX + 9-phenanthrylsulfate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-phenanthrol + X-SO3(-) -eq- HX + 2-phenanthrylsulfate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetyl-CoA + propanoate -eq- acetate + propanoyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetyl-CoA + (E)-glutaconate -eq- acetate + glutaconyl-1-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1-oxa-2-oxocycloheptane + H2O -eq- 6-hydroxyhexanoate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  4-sulfolactone + OH- -eq- HSO3(-) + maleylacetate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3,4-dihydrocoumarin + H2O -eq- 3-(2-hydroxyphenyl) propionate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  butyrolactone + H2O -eq- 4-hydroxybutanoate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  6-oxo-2-hydroxycyclohexane-1-carboxyl-CoA + H2O -eq- 3-hydroxypimeloyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-ketocyclohexane-1-carboxyl-CoA + H2O -eq- pimeloyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-formylglutathione + H(2)O -eq- formate + glutathione + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  4-hydroxybenzoyl-CoA + H(2)O -eq- 4-hydroxybenzoate + CoA + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  2'-hydroxybiphenyl-2-sulfinate + H(2)O -eq- biphenyl-2-ol + sulfite.
Catalysis of the reaction -  dodecyl sulfate + H2O -eq- sulfate + H+ + 1-dodecanol.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of the ether in chloro- or hydroxyepoxypropane to produce chloropropane diol or glycerol. Acts on R enantiomers.
Catalysis of the reaction -  phenanthrene-9,10-oxide + H2O -eq- trans-9R,10R-dihydrodiolphenanthrene.

Catalysis of the reaction -  limonene-1,2-epoxide + H2O -eq- limonene-1,2-diol. Other substrates include alicyclic and 1-methyl-substituted epoxides, such as 1-methylcyclohexene oxide, indene oxide and cyclohexene oxide.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of the ether in chloro-, bromo- or hydroxyepoxypropane to produce a chloro- or bromopropane diol or glycerol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  phenanthrene-3,4-oxide + H2O -eq- trans-3,4-dihydrodiolphenanthrene.
Catalysis of the reaction -  phenanthrene-1,2-oxide + H2O -eq- trans-1,2-dihydrodiolphenanthrene.
Catalysis of the reaction -  iprodione + OH- -eq- 3,5-dichlorophenylcarboximide + N-isopropylcarbamate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (3,5-dichlorophenylurea)acetate + OH- -eq- 3,5-dichloroaniline + N-carboxyglycine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  biuret + H2O -eq- urea + CO2 + NH3.
